QUERY: puberty blockers teenagers safe
DATE: 12-03-2024
Puberty blockers are generally considered safe when used appropriately: [1, 2, 3]
Effectiveness
Puberty blockers have been used safely for decades to treat children with precocious puberty and endometriosis. They are also a key medical option for youth who identify as transgender or are unsure and want to explore possibilities before the development of permanent secondary sex characteristics. [1, 2]
Bone health
Puberty blockers can impact bone density, but bone density generally returns to normal after discontinuing the medication. To support bone health, you can take vitamin D and calcium supplements, and do weight-bearing exercises. [3]
Side effects
Side effects of puberty blockers include: [4]
Swelling at the site of the shot [4]
Weight gain [4]
Hot flashes [4]
Headaches [4]
Mood changes [4]

Some concerns about puberty blockers include: [5, 6, 7]
Long-term side effects: Some say that puberty blockers may cause serious permanent side effects, including osteoporosis, mood disorders, seizures, and cognitive impairment. [5]
Informed consent: Some researchers question whether adolescents are able to give truly informed consent to medications that interrupt the construction of the neural architecture that underpins complex decision making. [6]
Impaired fertility: Puberty blockers can impair fertility and sexual functioning. [7]

